This paper discusses an alternative approach to ranking journals based on information from social and mainstream media sources. The data comes from altmetric.com, which identifies mentions of individual academic papers in sources such as Twitter, Facebook, blogs, and news outlets. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information retrieval (cs.SI, cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
